comment: Global offset is -1.5 to compensate glass-supported homing procedure. 800 µL T3. Completed prints with mediocre surface defects. 2/7 prints with holes due to captured air bubbles. Dipping of printhead in DPBS for washing. Minor damage to bottom sides during collection from printhead with spatula. Post-curing 30 min in FormCure at RT in petri dish with DPBS. Packing in 2 ml Eppi with DPBS.

Global offset is -1.5. 800 µL T3. Printhead sticks strongly to FEP film after printing. Trial to remove it tears all prints apart: parts stick to printhead, parts to FEP film -> the film in vat AL_005 seems to be a different product than that of previously used blue metal ink vat i.e. less non-adhesive -> switch back to blue metal ink vat. Moreover, decision to reduce disc size to 6 mm (96-well plate).
next steps: Switch out ink vat. Create new CAD with smaller discs. Repeat print (see Log220601-03)
